60std::unique_ptr<PrefetchCache::Entry> PrefetchCache::take(const URL& url)
61{
62 auto* resources = m_sessionPrefetches.get();
63 if (!resources)
64 return nullptr;
65 m_sessionExpirationList.removeAllMatching([&url] (const auto& tuple) {
66 return std::get<0>(tuple) == url;
67 });
68 auto entry = resources->take(url);
69 ASSERT(!entry || !entry->response.httpHeaderField(WebCore::HTTPHeaderName::Vary).contains("Cookie"));
70 return entry;
71}

75void PrefetchCache::store(const URL& requestUrl, WebCore::ResourceResponse&& response, RefPtr<WebCore::SharedBuffer>&& buffer)
76{
77 if (!m_sessionPrefetches)
78 m_sessionPrefetches = makeUnique<PrefetchEntriesMap>();
79 auto addResult = m_sessionPrefetches->add(requestUrl, makeUnique<PrefetchCache::Entry>(WTFMove(response), WTFMove(buffer)));
80 // Limit prefetches for same url to 1.
81 if (!addResult.isNewEntry)
82 return;
83 m_sessionExpirationList.append(std::make_tuple(requestUrl, WallTime::now()));
84 if (!m_expirationTimer.isActive())
85 m_expirationTimer.startOneShot(expirationTimeout);
86}

93 m_sessionPrefetches->set(requestUrl, makeUnique<PrefetchCache::Entry>(WTFMove(redirectResponse), WTFMove(redirectRequest)));

97}

99void PrefetchCache::clearExpiredEntries()
100{
101 auto timeout = WallTime::now();
102 while (!m_sessionExpirationList.isEmpty()) {
103 auto [requestUrl, timestamp] = m_sessionExpirationList.first();
104 auto* resources = m_sessionPrefetches.get();
105 ASSERT(resources);
106 ASSERT(resources->contains(requestUrl));
107 auto elapsed = timeout - timestamp;
108 if (elapsed > expirationTimeout) {
109 resources->remove(requestUrl);
110 m_sessionExpirationList.removeFirst();
111 } else {
112 m_expirationTimer.startOneShot(expirationTimeout - elapsed);
113 break;
114 }
115 }
